          {
            "after_answer": "odd",
            "before_answer": "odd",
            "gold_answer": "Let $f(x)$ and $g(x)$ be odd functions so $f(-x) = -f(x)$ and $g(-x) = -g(x).$  Let $h(x) = f(x) + g(x).$  Then\n\\[h(-x) = f(-x) + g(-x) = -f(x) - g(x) = -h(x)\\]so $h(x)$ is $\\boxed{\\text{odd}}.$",
            "id": "4809"
